----------------------------------------------

Welcome back to The Daily Courant, your afternoon compilation of
Puck=E2=80=99s best new reporting.

=C2=A0

First up today, Lauren Sherman dissects the latest changes within the Chane=
l empire as the Matthieu Blazy era approaches: the Wertheimer family=E2=80=
=99s restructuring of the business, the painful layoffs and employee exits,=
 and, most tellingly, the appointment of Teresa Ko (a.k.a. the =E2=80=9CI.P=
=2EO. queen=E2=80=9D) to the board. Is a
public offering on the horizon?=C2=A0

Plus, below the fold: Peter Hamby takes stock of the tech billionaires who =
were front and center at Trump=E2=80=99s inauguration. Scott Mendelson rumi=
nates on the five biggest themes keeping Hollywood executives up at night. =
On Somebody=E2=80=99s Gotta Win, Tara Palmeri is joined by Axios=E2=80=99s =
Marc Caputo to separate Trump=E2=80=99s inauguration rhetoric from the
viability of his agenda. On Fashion People, Lauren connects with The New Yo=
rk Times=E2=80=99s Sapna Maheshwari to discuss what the current TikTok chao=
s means for fashion brands. And on The Powers That Be, Peter rings up Bill =
Cohan for a sobering analysis of the first family=E2=80=99s cynically timed=
 launch of multibillion-dollar memecoins.

